        "comment": "20 to 30 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, fell in the past few hours. 20 to 30 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, will fall until the afternoon. <br/> The wind will be storm force. The wind will transport the new snow significantly. Deep wind slabs will form. <br/> <br/> The new snow and wind slabs are lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack above the tree line. The old snowpack will be weakly bonded, especially on west, north and east facing slopes above approximately 2200 m, and on south facing slopes at elevated altitudes."
